				)
			)
		)
		(property "Description" "Codec TX series-R / OUTP abs-max protection (2.2k): OUTP -> R26 -> C14 -> TALK_BRIDGE. Limits the OUTP clamp current when K1's make steps +12V (P2) onto TALK_BRIDGE and C14 couples that edge back to OUTP - D13 (BAT54SW) clamps OUTP to [AGND-0.3, AVDD+0.3] and absorbs the ~3.9mA (sim invariant B1). Also isolates the DAC from the C14 load. TX level is a firmware digital-volume trim - the codec far exceeds the WF26's passive 16-ohm transducer-mic level."
			(at 203.2 220.98 0)
			(hide yes)
			(show_name no)
			(do_not_autoplace no)
			(effects
				(font
